  "prompt": "What is trauma?",
  "response": "Trauma is an emotional response to a distressing or disturbing event that overwhelms an individual's ability to cope, resulting in feelings of helplessness, fear, and horror. Traumatic experiences can range from one-time incidents such as accidents, natural disasters, or violent attacks to ongoing, chronic experiences like abuse, neglect, or warfare. The impact of trauma can vary greatly from person to person and can lead to a range of symptoms and disorders, including post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), depression, anxiety, and substance abuse. Treatment for trauma often involves therapy and, in some cases, medication to help individuals process and recover from their experiences.",
